title: Resin Kangling
description:
Kangling translated as "leg" (kang) "flute" (ling), is the Tibetan name for a trumpet or horn made
out of a human tibia or femur, used in Tibetan Buddhism for various chöd rituals as well as funerals
performed by a chöpa. Size chart (Length) Small 8.65" Medium 11.4" Large 13.38" *approximately
